# E2E tests for Booking endpoints (VS Code REST Client)

### Create a new booking (valid payload)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1",
  "passengerName": "John Doe"
}

### Create another booking for the same flight (valid)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1",
  "passengerName": "Jane Smith"
}

### Get all bookings (no filter)
GET http://localhost:8080/bookings
Accept: application/json

### Get bookings filtered by flightId
GET http://localhost:8080/bookings?flightId=f1
Accept: application/json

### Get bookings filtered by passengerName
GET http://localhost:8080/bookings?passengerName=John%20Doe
Accept: application/json

### Get bookings filtered by both flightId and passengerName
GET http://localhost:8080/bookings?flightId=f1&passengerName=John%20Doe
Accept: application/json



### Create a booking with missing flightId (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "passengerName": "Alice Johnson"
}

### Create a booking with invalid flightId (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "invalid-flight-id",
  "passengerName": "Bob Brown"
}

### Create a booking with missing passengerName (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1"
}

### Create a booking with empty passengerName (error case)
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1",
  "passengerName": ""
}

### Create bookings until flight is full (capacity test)
# Note: Default rocket "r1" has capacity 10
# Create multiple bookings to test capacity validation
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1",
  "passengerName": "Passenger 3"
}

### Create one more booking after capacity is reached (error case)
# This should fail if flight is already full
POST http://localhost:8080/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "flightId": "f1",
  "passengerName": "Passenger Overflow"
}
